SEMDL Help Topic: reference set

Usage:
- `ssd set path:<id>.<field> <value> <file>`
- `ssd set path:<id>.<field> <value> --dry-run <file>`
- `ssd set path:<id>.<field> <value> --stdout <file>`
- `ssd set path:<id>.<field> <value> --out <output-file> <file>`
- `ssd set path:<id>.<field> <value> --out <output-file> --dry-run <file>`
- `ssd set meta:<id>.<field> <value> <file>`
- `ssd set meta:<id>.<field> <value> --dry-run <file>`
- `ssd set meta:<id>.<field> <value> --stdout <file>`
- `ssd set meta:<id>.<field> <value> --out <output-file> <file>`
- `ssd set meta:<id>.<field> <value> --out <output-file> --dry-run <file>`
- `ssd set id:<id> <field> <value> <file>`
- `ssd set id:<id> <field> <value> --dry-run <file>`
- `ssd set id:<id> <field> <value> --stdout <file>`
- `ssd set id:<id> <field> <value> --out <output-file> <file>`
- `ssd set id:<id> <field> <value> --out <output-file> --dry-run <file>`

- `ssd set id:<id>,id:<id>,... <field> <value> <file>`
- `ssd set id:<id>,id:<id>,... <field> <value> --dry-run <file>`
- `ssd set id:<id>,id:<id>,... <field> <value> --stdout <file>`
- `ssd set id:<id>,id:<id>,... <field> <value> --out <output-file> <file>`
- `ssd set id:<id>,id:<id>,... <field> <value> --out <output-file> --dry-run <file>`

- `ssd set type:<kind> <field> <value> --allow-multi <file>`
- `ssd set type:<kind> <field> <value> --allow-multi --dry-run <file>`
- `ssd set type:<kind> <field> <value> --allow-multi --stdout <file>`
- `ssd set type:<kind> <field> <value> --allow-multi --out <output-file> <file>`
- `ssd set type:<kind> <field> <value> --allow-multi --out <output-file> --dry-run <file>`

Purpose:
- Apply, preview, or emit one target field update, or one explicit id-list / type allow-multi inline field update set, in inline structure or sidecar metadata.
- `path:` and current `id:` updates use canonical inline `.ssd` for `--stdout` and `--out`.
- explicit id lists are limited to comma-separated `id:` atoms and currently preserve inline-only id field ownership.
- `type:<kind>` set is limited to inline-owned fields and currently requires `--allow-multi` even when one target matches.
- `meta:` updates use canonical sidecar `.ssm` for `--stdout` and `--out`.

Related help:
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help recipes wrong-layer`

Sample:
- `ssd set meta:A1.confidence 0.91 docs/examples/minimal.ssd`
- `ssd set path:A1.label 売上報告書 --stdout docs/examples/minimal.ssd`
